meanings.definition: A person or thing that has little or no influence or importance.
meanings.sent1: In the group project, unfortunately, I was just a nonfactor.
meanings.sent2: The small rock was a nonfactor in the landslide.
meanings.sent3: The silent toy robot was a nonfactor in the noisy playroom.
meanings.sent4: His opinion was like a nonfactor in the heated debate.
meanings.sent5: The background extras were mere nonfactors in the movie scene.

meanings.definition: Not contributing to a particular result or outcome.
meanings.sent1: Her absence was nonfactor in the final decision.
meanings.sent2: The broken compass was a nonfactor in their journey.
meanings.sent3: The expired coupon was a nonfactor in the shopping spree.
meanings.sent4: The old map was a nonfactor in their modern navigation.
meanings.sent5: The unplugged device was a nonfactor in the smart home system.
